<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15752">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Signs%20Signals%20Codes.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15775">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the importance of signs, signals, and codes,
      and why people need these different methods of communication. Briefly
      discuss the history and development of signs, signals, and codes. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/rTGShWIryMQ" target="_blank"
        >History of Communication: From Cave Paintings to TikTok (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15777">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain the importance of signaling in emergency communications. Discuss
      with your counselor the types of emergency or distress signals one might
      use to attract airborne search-and-rescue personnel if lost in the
      outdoors or trying to summon assistance during a disaster. Illustrate
      these signaling examples by the use of photos or drawings. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Gtp-wVJR348" target="_blank"
        >Signaling in Emergencies—A Beginners Guide to Getting Noticed
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/VGxWPZ36kFc" target="_blank"
        >How To Send a Rescue Signal by Semaphore (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15753">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15753 mb-requirement-id-15754">
        (a) Describe what Morse code is and the various means by which it can be
        sent. Spell your first name using Morse code. Send or receive a message
        of six to 10 words using Morse code. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/iy8BaMs_JuI" target="_blank"
          >How Does Morse Code Work? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://morsecode.world/international/morse2.html"
          target="_blank"
          >International Morse Code (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15753 mb-requirement-id-15755">
        (b) Describe what American Sign Language (ASL) is and how it is used
        today. Spell your first name using American Sign Language. Send or
        receive a message of six to 10 words using ASL. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6_gXiBe9y9A" target="_blank"
          >Learn ASL Alphabet (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wa0nxppMJ-Q" target="_blank"
          >A Few Things To Know About American Sign Language (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15756">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15756 mb-requirement-id-15757">
        (a) Give your counselor a brief explanation about semaphore, why it is
        used, how it is used, and where it is used. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FrgQV59LEHk" target="_blank"
          >Semaphore (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://s28681.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Semaphore_Chart_BlueJacketsManual_24821763802.jpg"
          target="_blank"
          >Semaphore Chart (photo)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JVBLDDpIFCA" target="_blank"
          >How To Use Semaphore Flags in a Treasure Hunt (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15756 mb-requirement-id-15758">
        (b) Explain to your counselor the difference between semaphore flags and
        nautical flags. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7i1tyWoKIb8" target="_blank"
          >How To Read Signal Flags! (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1zwUsznJMds" target="_blank"
          >Nautical Flag Word Search Activity (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DH8hyZUnPPs" target="_blank"
          >Crack the Code of NATO's Flag Signals (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15756 mb-requirement-id-15779">
        (c) After 4(a) and 4(b) have been completed, do the following:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15779 mb-requirement-id-15780">
        (1) Spell your first name using semaphore. Send or receive a message of
        six to 10 words using semaphore.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15779 mb-requirement-id-15781">
        (2) Using illustrations or photographs, identify 10 examples of nautical
        flags and discuss their importance.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15759">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Explain the braille reading technique and how it helps individuals with
      sight impairment to communicate. Then do the following: <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/eRFGNwKACY0" target="_blank"
        >The Story of Reading Braille (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15759 mb-requirement-id-15760">
        (a) Either by sight or by touch, identify the letters of the braille
        alphabet that spell your name. By sight or touch, decode a braille
        message at least six words long. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/IFJGr29oWso" target="_blank"
          >Write and Read Braille (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15759 mb-requirement-id-15761">
        (b) Create a message in braille at least six words long, and share this
        with your counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15762">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15762 mb-requirement-id-15763">
        (a) Describe to your counselor six sound-only signals that are in use
        today. Discuss the pros and cons of using sound signals versus other
        types of signals. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tnP9NwT_Vgk" target="_blank"
          >How To Use Sound Signaling Devices on a Boat (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/_1jJYPRwYxg" target="_blank"
          >Ship Whistle Signals Explained—Fog, Anchor, Warnings (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jKJ0vpGRlVs" target="_blank"
          >Musical Communication in the Navy (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15762 mb-requirement-id-15764">
        (b) Demonstrate to your counselor six different silent Scout signals.
        Use these Scout signals to direct the movements and actions of your
        patrol or troop. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://troopleader.scouting.org/ceremonies/silent-scout-signals/"
          target="_blank"
          >Silent Scout Signals (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Signs%2C%20Signals%2C%20and%20Codes/scout_silent_hand_signals_chart.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Scout Silent Hand Signals (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15778">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      On a Scout outing, lay out a trail for your patrol or troop to follow.
      Cover at least one mile in distance and use at least six different trail
      signs and markers. After the Scouts have completed the trail, follow the
      Leave No Trace Seven Principles and the Outdoor Code by replacing or
      returning trail markers to their original locations. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Signs%2C%20Signals%2C%20and%20Codes/generic-resources-tracking-signs.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >Tracking Signs (PDF)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.tiktok.com/@evangoesoutside/video/7128048670083353902?is_from_webapp=1&amp;sender_device=pc"
        target="_blank"
        >Understanding the Debate on Rock Cairns: Environmental Impact and
        Folklore Explained (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15765">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      For THREE of the following activities, demonstrate five signals each. Tell
      what the signals mean and why they are used:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15765 mb-requirement-id-15766">
        (a) Sports official's hand signs/signals <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NMcp3rSQXs8" target="_blank"
          >Soccer Referee Hand Signals (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/RaeJ8BzOdJQ" target="_blank"
          >Basketball Referee Penalties and Signals (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/x039Ia39ZYU" target="_blank"
          >How To Know What the Referee Is Signaling While Watching Football
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15765 mb-requirement-id-15767">
        (b) Heavy-equipment operator's hand signals <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/t4dl5zAE9oc" target="_blank"
          >Basic Hand Signals for Heavy Equipment Operators (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/trBPvOC8Jts" target="_blank"
          >Cascadia Tech Excavator Hand Signal (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15765 mb-requirement-id-15768">
        (c) Aircraft carrier catapult crew signals <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/As7zQPkkv8c" target="_blank"
          >Aircraft Carrier's Crew Hand Signals Explained—Preflight and Launch
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15765 mb-requirement-id-15769">
        (d) Cyclist's hand signals <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/prYMM7D2qF8&amp;t=41" target="_blank"
          >How To Use Hand Signals While Cycling | Essential Group Ride
          Communication for Bike Riders (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15765 mb-requirement-id-15770">
        (e) An activity selected by you and your counselor
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15771">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Share with your counselor 10 examples of symbols used in everyday life.
      Design your own symbol. Share it with your counselor and explain what it
      means. Then do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15771 mb-requirement-id-15772">
        (a) Show examples of 10 traffic signs and explain their meaning.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JU0PXiLPw3U" target="_blank"
          >Understanding Road Signs || Traffic Signs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fMIGRMVY4nQ" target="_blank"
          >Learning Traffic Signs/Road Signs With Their Meanings (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15771 mb-requirement-id-15773">
        (b) Using a topographical map, explain what a map legend is and discuss
        its importance. Point out 10 map symbols and explain the meaning of
        each. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CoVcRxza8nI" target="_blank"
          >How To Read a Topo Map (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15771 mb-requirement-id-15774">
        (c) Discuss text-message symbols and why they are commonly used. Give
        examples of your favorite 10 text symbols or emoticons. Then see if your
        parent, guardian, or counselor can identify the meaning or usage of each
        symbol. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TKzw4Y_7f_At" target="_blank"
          >What Do Emojis Mean? | Understanding Emoji Meanings and Usage
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15776">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      Briefly discuss the history of secret code writing (cryptography). Make up
      your own secret code and write a message of up to 25 words using this
      code. Share the message with a friend or fellow Scout. Then share the
      message and code key with your counselor and discuss the effectiveness of
      your code. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/xNevRfldNZ0" target="_blank"
        >A Short History of Codes (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/J1o2zo6HleY" target="_blank"
        >Cryptography: The Vigenere Cipher (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/vjGhiac85h4" target="_blank"
        >The History of Crypto Goes Further Back Than You Think (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
